	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)">Office of <persName>ALLEN &#38; CO.</persName>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>82 BEAVER STREET</placeName>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>NEW YORK</placeName>&#44; <date>March 1 1865</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev&#58; I Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir and friend.  Yours is at<lb/> hand&#44; and I will attend to your<lb/> commission&#44; to <sic>morrow</sic>&#44; with much pleasure.<lb/>  I will see you I hope&#44; on <date>Sunday</date> next&#44;<lb/> and make return of the <placeName>Savannah</placeName> collection&#44;<lb/> and also confer with you on the subject&#44;<lb/> I have so far collected say &#36;400&#61;.<lb/>  I saw <persName>Rev JJL</persName> yesterday PM.  He feels<lb/> a little put out&#44; that I should have<lb/> had the start of the affair&#44; more about<lb/> it when I see you.  <persName>Henry Abhm</persName><lb/> <sic>desire</sic> kind regards.  Very truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">M. M. Allen</persName></p>
		</body>
